<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-31T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="692" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.53/1–2050: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Turkey</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-31T17:00:00-05:00">March
                                        31, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>140. Treas Dept reports disturbing increase heroin addiction US
                                cities. Istanbul’s desp 38, Jan 20,<note n="1" xml:id="d692fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> appears confirm Treas opinion major part this
                                heroin originates Istanbul.</p>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> requested inform appropriate
                                Turk auths US Govt concerned notwithstanding excellent work Istanbul
                                police and suggest desirability continued close cooperation Istanbul
                                police and US Bureau Narcotics. Latter ready send competent agent
                                visit Istanbul collaborate <pb facs="1270" n="1248" xml:id="pg_1248"/> police in order furnish names and addresses suspected traffickers
                                and for other activities. Inquire discreetly whether Turk Govt wld
                                be disposed extend invitation this purpose.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>